 Thanks for using this app Thrusday Avoid injuries. Carefully follow the instructions, for each of the workouts, to prevent injuries. Get adequate sleep of around 7 -8 hours. Insufficient sleep can lead to heart diseases, high blood pressure, diabetes, obesity etc. For your workout, buy shoes that are comfortable. It is better to go for training shoes, as it will give you the comfort and the grip that you are looking for. Replace shoes once in six months. Exercise in the morning. Exercising in the morning promotes weight loss, prevents diabetes, lowers blood pressure, keeps you active throughout the day and has many more benefits. Have a complete breakfast. Let the breakfast be the heaviest meal in the day. After a good night sleep, you need a nutritious breakfast to kick start your day. Drink sufficient quantity of water. Men should consume about 3.7 liters of water per day and women should consume about 2.7 liters of water per day. Always make sure, you have a rest day in between your workout days. Let every fourth day be a rest day. Taking rest will help your muscles to grow. Avoid junk food as it is high in calories. Junk food can cause obesity, heart diseases and other health conditions. Eat a healthy diet. Consume protein rich and low calorie food, as it gives you sufficient strength during workouts and builds muscles. Increase your fiber intake. Fiber intake aids digestion and also helps to lose weight and improves your heart health.
